    "updated_at": "2015-08-14T03:40:14Z",
    "body": "Sorry to append to this issue, but I've been also encountering issues with MSVS 2015, will try to downgrade to 2013 and see. \nBut on another node, I've been wondering on what version of Node.js (or io.js) I should be when attempting to build module that require to be rebuilt with node-gyp (I assume those are native modules). \n\nIt would be nice if the windows releases gave information on what version of Node was used. I might be blind, maybe it's straight in my face.\n"
